{
  "stem": "14060.4",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And therefore, that event is interesting how a Jew from Hungary, without fear, could go up, like my father did, to bring his brother up, which was no problem.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "As it happens, this uncle of mine obviously couldn't practice as a doctor officially in Hungary and went up to Budapest where he started to manufacture ladies' cosmetic products, which he was very successful with.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In fact, at the end of it, he was not deported to Auschwitz or any camps, but got caught up in the Munka Tabor and eventually was taken to Felixdorf, which is a, a small place in Austria, also was kind of a camp, of concentration camp, of a minor size.",
      "word_count": 51
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he survived there.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He went back to Budapest after the war and had a wife and two children.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The wife and he died, unfortunately-- died rather early, 1960.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I took him out to Australia, where I lived after the war between 1951 and '58.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I brought him up after the '56 revolution.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And unfortunately, within four years, he died.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "He suddenly had a heart attack.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "His wife survived in Warsaw, subsequently died.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "She had leukemia or something.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And the two children, two cousins, do exist today in Melbourne, Australia.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "The other-- to do with the Austrian Anschluss, which is clearly in my mind, there were Jews left in Vienna right up till late 1942.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Most of the Austrian Jews were taken to Poland because of-- the time it started in Austria was before the killing machinery was put into effect and were sent to what they called Litzmannstadt, which is Lodz, the Lodz Ghetto.",
      "word_count": 40
    }
  ],
